1
00:00:00,960 --> 00:00:02,795
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

2
00:00:02,837 --> 00:00:04,964
MAGISTRATE:
BRING IN THE PRISONER.

3
00:00:06,882 --> 00:00:09,092
[SPECTATORS CHANTING "JAGH"]

4
00:00:21,814 --> 00:00:23,941
YOU STAND ACCUSED OF CONSPIRING

5
00:00:23,983 --> 00:00:26,360
AGAINST THE KLINGON EMPIRE.

6
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,236
HOW DO YOU RESPOND?

7
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,905
ARCHER: I'M NOT GUILTY.

8
00:00:29,947 --> 00:00:31,866
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

9
00:00:31,907 --> 00:00:33,909
MAGISTRATE: WHEN THIS TRIBUNAL
CONVENES TOMORROW,

10
00:00:33,951 --> 00:00:36,704
YOU WILL BE GIVEN A CHANCE
TO PROVE YOUR INNOCENCE.

11
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:40,916
IF YOU CANNOT,
THERE IS ONLY ONE PUNISHMENT.

12
00:00:40,958 --> 00:00:44,043
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

13
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:48,215
[SPECTATORS CHANTING "JAGH"]

14
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:57,265
SINGER: ♪ IT'S BEEN
A LONG ROAD ♪

15
00:00:58,851 --> 00:01:02,062
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

16
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:05,900
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

17
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:09,862
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

18
00:01:09,904 --> 00:01:14,199
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

19
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:17,661
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

20
00:01:17,703 --> 00:01:21,498
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

21
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:24,752
♪ NO, THEY'RE
NOT GONNA CHANGE MY MIND ♪

22
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:27,629
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

23
00:01:27,671 --> 00:01:29,631
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

24
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:32,885
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

25
00:01:32,927 --> 00:01:37,806
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

26
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:40,642
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

27
00:01:40,684 --> 00:01:45,689
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

28
00:01:45,731 --> 00:01:48,400
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA
BEND OR BREAK ME ♪

29
00:01:48,442 --> 00:01:53,948
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

30
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:55,282
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

31
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:57,701
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

32
00:01:57,743 --> 00:02:01,789
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

33
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:05,834
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

34
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,948
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

35
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:41,244
GUARD: YOU HAVE FIVE MINUTES.

36
00:02:42,997 --> 00:02:44,832
ARCHER: GLAD YOU COULD DROP BY.

37
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:46,166
PHLOX: HOW ARE YOU?

38
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:48,335
ARCHER: I'VE BEEN BETTER.

39
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:51,130
PHLOX: I WASN'T SURE
IF I'D FIND YOU ALIVE.

40
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:54,257
ARCHER: THEY PROMISED ME A TRIAL
BEFORE THE EXECUTION.

41
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:57,636
SOMETHING WRONG?

42
00:02:57,678 --> 00:02:59,680
PHLOX: XENOPOLYCYTHEMIA
CAN BE HIGHLY CONTAGIOUS.

43
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:03,350
I'M SURPRISED THEY
HAVEN'T PUT YOU IN ISOLATION.

44
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:05,310
ANY RESIDUAL SYMPTOMS?

45
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,895
FEVER, DIZZINESS?

46
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:08,939
ARCHER: JUST A SCRATCHY THROAT.

47
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:12,317
PHLOX: LET'S HAVE A LOOK.

48
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,571
ARCHER: WHEN DID YOU GET HERE?

49
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:17,865
PHLOX: TWO DAYS AGO,

50
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,825
BUT THEY REFUSED
TO LET US SEE YOU.

51
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,785
ARCHER: ENEMIES OF THE STATE
AREN'T ALLOWED VISITORS.

52
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:24,079
PHLOX: HMM. T'POL WAS
FINALLY ABLE TO CONVINCE THEM

53
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:25,831
THAT YOUR CONDITION

54
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:27,749
NECESSITATED A VISIT
FROM YOUR DOCTOR.

55
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,127
ARCHER: VERY THOUGHTFUL OF HER.
PHLOX: SHE SENDS HER REGARDS.

56
00:03:30,169 --> 00:03:31,795
AND SHE WANTED ME TO
ASSURE YOU THAT STARFLEET

57
00:03:31,837 --> 00:03:33,338
AND THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND

58
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,174
ARE DOING EVERYTHING POSSIBLE
TO GET YOU RELEASED.

59
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,800
ARCHER:
AREN'T THEY HAVING ANY LUCK?

60
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:38,177
PHLOX: NOT YET.

61
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:39,678
BUT SHE AND COMMANDER TUCKER

62
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,596
HAVE BEGUN EXPLORING
OTHER OPTIONS

63
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,016
FOR REGAINING YOUR FREEDOM.

64
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:49,063
ARCHER: WHEN THIS IS OVER--

65
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,731
WHATEVER THE OUTCOME--

66
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:52,607
I'M COUNTING ON THEM

67
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:55,443
TO GET "ENTERPRISE" SAFELY
OUT OF KLINGON TERRITORY.

68
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:58,655
PHLOX: I'LL LET THEM KNOW.

69
00:04:00,074 --> 00:04:02,492
HOW ARE YOUR ACCOMMODATIONS?

70
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:06,413
ARCHER: NOT SO BAD.

71
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:09,083
CAN'T SAY I'M A BIG FAN
OF KLINGON CUISINE.

72
00:04:09,124 --> 00:04:11,043
PHLOX:
IT MAY NOT APPEAR APPETIZING,

73
00:04:11,085 --> 00:04:13,336
BUT IT, UH, SEEMS LIKE
A GOOD SOURCE OF PROTEIN.

74
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:15,422
I SUGGEST YOU EAT IT.

75
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:19,843
KOLOS: IS HE INFECTIOUS?

76
00:04:19,885 --> 00:04:21,803
PHLOX: I DON'T BELIEVE SO.
KOLOS: THEN RETURN TO YOUR SHIP.

77
00:04:21,845 --> 00:04:23,889
PHLOX: I'D LIKE TO RUN
SOME MORE TESTS.

78
00:04:23,931 --> 00:04:26,349
KOLOS:
YOU'RE NOT HERE TO TREAT HIM.

79
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:32,814
ARCHER:
THANKS FOR THE HOUSE CALL, DOC.

80
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:35,192
PHLOX: I'M SURE
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

81
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:40,739
KOLOS: I'M KOLOS, YOUR ADVOCATE.

82
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:42,616
ARCHER: JONATHAN ARCHER.

83
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,076
KOLOS: HMM.

84
00:04:44,118 --> 00:04:45,786
THE TRIBUNAL'S ABOUT TO BEGIN.

85
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:48,038
ARCHER: WE HAVEN'T EVEN
DISCUSSED WHAT HAPPENED.

86
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,748
KOLOS: I'M FAMILIAR
WITH THE CHARGES.

87
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,374
ARCHER: WELL, I'M NOT FAMILIAR

88
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,168
WITH YOUR JUSTICE SYSTEM.

89
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:55,545
WHAT CAN I EXPECT OUT THERE?

90
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,338
KOLOS: NOW THAT
YOU'VE BEEN CHARGED,

91
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:59,507
THE EVIDENCE AGAINST YOU
WILL BE PRESENTED.

92
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:02,136
ARCHER: WHEN DO I GET A CHANCE
TO TESTIFY?

93
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:05,055
KOLOS:
I WILL CONDUCT YOUR DEFENSE.

94
00:05:05,097 --> 00:05:06,681
ARCHER: HOW CAN YOU DO THAT

95
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,767
WHEN YOU HAVEN'T HEARD
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED?

96
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,103
KOLOS: I KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

97
00:05:11,145 --> 00:05:14,397
YOU MUSTN'T
SPEAK DURING THE TRIBUNAL.

98
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,233
I'LL SPEAK FOR YOU.

99
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:24,866
[CROWD CHANTING "JAGH"]

100
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:40,423
ARCHER: WHAT ARE THEY SAYING?

101
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,801
KOLOS: "ENEMY."

102
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:45,179
ARCHER:
I HOPE THEY'RE NOT THE JURY.

103
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:47,181
KOLOS: THERE IS NO JURY.

104
00:05:47,222 --> 00:05:50,225
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

105
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,234
ARCHER: WHO'S THAT?

106
00:05:59,276 --> 00:06:01,862
KOLOS: PROSECUTOR ORAK.

107
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,822
HIS SUCCESS IS WELL KNOWN.

108
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:05,824
ARCHER: WHAT ABOUT YOU?

109
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:08,327
WHAT'S YOUR SUCCESS RATE?

110
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:13,456
KOLOS: I PERFORM MY DUTY.

111
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,959
[LOUD SHOUTS]

112
00:06:22,174 --> 00:06:25,010
MAGISTRATE:
THIS TRIBUNAL IS CONVENED.

113
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:27,054
STRENGTH TO THE EMPIRE!

114
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:30,307
PROSECUTOR ORAK,
YOU MAY PROCEED.

115
00:06:30,349 --> 00:06:34,061
ORAK:
I CALL DURAS, SON OF TORAL.

116
00:06:39,024 --> 00:06:41,400
CAPTAIN DURAS,
TELL THE TRIBUNAL

117
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,402
ABOUT YOUR ENCOUNTER
WITH THE ACCUSED.

118
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:45,739
DURAS: I AM NO LONGER A CAPTAIN.

119
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,699
ORAK: EXPLAIN.

120
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,826
DURAS:
I AM A SECOND WEAPONS OFFICER

121
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:53,372
SERVING ON THE TY'GOKOR
DEFENSE PERIMETER.

122
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:55,082
ORAK:
THE DURAS I CALLED TO TESTIFY

123
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,876
IS COMMANDER
OF THE BATTLE CRUISER "BORTAS."

124
00:06:57,918 --> 00:07:02,047
DURAS:
I WAS RECENTLY REDUCED IN RANK.

125
00:07:02,089 --> 00:07:04,507
ORAK:
A DISTINGUISHED KLINGON WARRIOR

126
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:08,011
STRIPPED OF HIS COMMAND.

127
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:09,930
DID THE ACCUSED HAVE ANYTHING

128
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:11,556
TO DO WITH YOUR DISGRACE?

129
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:13,058
DURAS: YES.

130
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:18,230
ORAK:
GO ON, WEAPONS OFFICER DURAS.

131
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:20,107
DURAS:
A GROUP OF REBELS HAD FLED

132
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:22,692
THE KLINGON PROTECTORATE
AT RAATOORAS.

133
00:07:22,734 --> 00:07:25,904
I WAS COMMANDED TO BRING
THESE TRAITORS TO JUSTICE.

134
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:27,614
WE'D FOLLOWED THEIR WARP TRAIL

135
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:31,076
TO A SYSTEM JUST OUTSIDE
KLINGON TERRITORY.

136
00:07:31,118 --> 00:07:32,702
OFFICER:
THEY'RE NEAR THE FIFTH PLANET.

137
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:34,288
ANOTHER VESSEL
IS DOCKED WITH THEM.

138
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:36,206
DURAS: SHOW ME.

139
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,542
WHAT KIND OF SHIP IS THAT?

140
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,044
OFFICER: UNKNOWN.

141
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:42,587
BUT THEY'VE
TAKEN THE REBELS ABOARD.

142
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:43,964
DURAS: ARMAMENTS?

143
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,341
OFFICER: TORPEDO LAUNCHERS
FORE AND AFT.

144
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:48,176
LOW-YIELD PARTICLE CANNONS.

145
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:50,095
WE CAN DEFEAT THEM EASILY.

146
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:51,721
DURAS: INTERCEPT.

147
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:53,140
OFFICER: THEY'RE SIGNALING US.

148
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:55,016
DURAS: VIEWER.

149
00:07:55,058 --> 00:07:57,644
IDENTIFY YOURSELF.

150
00:07:57,685 --> 00:08:01,273
ARCHER:<i> CAPTAIN ARCHER OF</i>
<i>THE BATTLE CRUISER</i> ENTERPRISE.

151
00:08:01,315 --> 00:08:03,566
DURAS: THE PEOPLE ABOARD YOUR
SHIP ARE WANTED FOR TREASON.

152
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:05,693
SURRENDER THEM IMMEDIATELY.

153
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,737
ARCHER:<i> BY WHOSE AUTHORITY?</i>

154
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:09,323
DURAS: THE CHANCELLOR
OF THE KLINGON HIGH COUNCIL.

155
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:10,782
ARCHER:
<i>I DON'T KNOW YOUR CHANCELLOR,</i>

156
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:12,492
<i>AND I DON'T GIVE A DAMN</i>
<i>WHAT HE WANTS.</i>

157
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,328
<i>I'VE FORMED AN ALLIANCE</i>
<i>WITH THESE PEOPLE,</i>

158
00:08:14,369 --> 00:08:16,830
<i>AND I'M GOING TO SUPPORT</i>
<i>THEIR REVOLT.</i>

159
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,791
DURAS: GIVE THEM TO ME NOW
OR I'LL DESTROY YOUR VESSEL.

160
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,626
ARCHER:<i> FIRE ONE SHOT,</i>

161
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:24,504
<i>AND YOU'LL BE JOINING YOUR</i>
<i>ANCESTORS IN THE AFTERLIFE.</i>

162
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:27,715
ORAK: HE REFUSED
TO SURRENDER THE REBELS?

163
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:29,384
DURAS: YES.

164
00:08:29,426 --> 00:08:31,594
ARCHER: I DIDN'T SAY
ANY OF THOSE THINGS.

165
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,180
CAN'T YOU OBJECT?

166
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,556
KOLOS: IT'S NOT IMPORTANT.

167
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:39,311
ORAK: AND HOW DID YOU
RESPOND TO ARCHER'S DEFIANCE?

168
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:41,021
DURAS: I PITIED HIM.

169
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:43,064
HE WAS ABOUT TO DIE IN DEFENSE

170
00:08:43,106 --> 00:08:44,941
OF THESE WRETCHED TRAITORS.

171
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:46,360
ARCHER: THEY WEREN'T TRAITORS.

172
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:48,153
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

173
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:49,779
MAGISTRATE: ADVOCATE, HAVEN'T
YOU INFORMED THE PRISONER

174
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,948
OF THE RULES OF THIS TRIBUNAL?

175
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,159
KOLOS: MY APOLOGIES, MAGISTRATE.

176
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:57,329
BE SILENT
OR YOU WILL BE REMOVED.

177
00:08:57,371 --> 00:08:58,997
ORAK: CONTINUE.

178
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:02,209
DURAS: I SHOWED HIM
MORE PATIENCE THAN HE DESERVED.

179
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:06,338
BUT OBVIOUSLY
HE WANTED BLOOD TO BE SPILLED.

180
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:09,341
DON'T BE A FOOL.
YOUR SHIP IS INFERIOR.

181
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:11,676
YOU WON'T SURVIVE
A BATTLE WITH US.

182
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:13,928
ARCHER:<i> DEATH TO THE EMPIRE.</i>

183
00:09:16,515 --> 00:09:18,350
DURAS: RETURN FIRE!

184
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,068
OFFICER: THEY'RE HEADING
FOR THE RING SYSTEM.

185
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:29,736
DURAS:
THE COWARD THINKS HE CAN HIDE.

186
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:31,363
PURSUE THEM!

187
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,585
WHERE ARE THEY?

188
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,254
ANSWER ME!

189
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:50,090
OFFICER: DEBRIS IS INTERFERING
WITH SENSORS.

190
00:09:53,218 --> 00:09:56,763
DURAS: THERE! TARGET
THEIR ENGINES! ALL WEAPONS!

191
00:10:20,287 --> 00:10:22,289
OFFICER: WE'VE LOST SENSORS.
SHIELDS ARE DOWN!

192
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:24,958
DURAS: MANUAL TARGETING! FIRE!

193
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:34,259
OFFICER: THEY'RE LEAVING ORBIT!

194
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,719
DURAS: FOLLOW THEM!
OFFICER: OUR ENGINES ARE DOWN.

195
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,389
[DURAS YELLS]

196
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:43,351
DURAS: IT TOOK US 3 HOURS
TO REPAIR OUR WARP DRIVE.

197
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:47,105
ORAK: BUT, OF COURSE,
BY THAT TIME, THEY WERE GONE.

198
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:48,689
YOU'RE FORTUNATE
YOUR FIRST OFFICER

199
00:10:48,731 --> 00:10:50,691
DIDN'T KILL YOU
FOR SUCH A FAILURE.

200
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,819
YOU'RE DISMISSED.

201
00:10:58,617 --> 00:11:00,619
ARCHER: YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO QUESTION HIM?

202
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,912
KOLOS: HE'D SAY NOTHING
THAT WOULD HELP YOU.

203
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:05,748
MAGISTRATE: DO YOU HAVE
ANY FURTHER EVIDENCE TO PRESENT?

204
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:07,708
ORAK: NO, MAGISTRATE.

205
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,711
DURAS' TESTIMONY IS CLEAR.

206
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:14,132
HE WAS ATTEMPTING
TO CARRY OUT HIS MISSION--

207
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:18,136
TO BRING ENEMIES
OF THE EMPIRE TO JUSTICE.

208
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:21,973
BUT THIS AGGRESSOR,
THIS HUMAN,

209
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:23,891
CONSPIRED WITH THEM

210
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:27,479
TO DISGRACE A PROUD WARRIOR
AND FOMENT REBELLION.

211
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:32,150
THERE CAN BE NO DOUBT
THAT HE IS OUR ENEMY AS WELL.

212
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:34,027
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

213
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:37,614
CAPTAIN ARCHER CLAIMS
TO BE INNOCENT!

214
00:11:37,656 --> 00:11:39,574
INNOCENT OF WHAT?

215
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:42,661
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

216
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:46,498
THIS TRIBUNAL HAS ALREADY
BEEN FAR TOO LENIENT.

217
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:48,875
WE HAVEN'T ACCUSED HIS CREW

218
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,377
OR HIS GOVERNMENT.

219
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,379
HE'S FORTUNATE
WE HAVEN'T DISPATCHED

220
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,755
A FLEET OF WARSHIPS
TO HIS HOMEWORLD!

221
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:57,342
BUT WE DO DEMAND
THAT HE BE HELD RESPONSIBLE

222
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,135
FOR THE CRIMES HE HAS COMMITTED.

223
00:11:59,177 --> 00:12:00,803
WE DEMAND THAT HE RECEIVE

224
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:04,432
THE MOST SEVERE PUNISHMENT
OUR LAWS DECREE!

225
00:12:04,474 --> 00:12:06,351
JAGH!

226
00:12:06,393 --> 00:12:09,103
[SPECTATORS CHANTING "JAGH"]

227
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,661
MAGISTRATE:
DO YOU HAVE A RESPONSE?

228
00:12:24,703 --> 00:12:27,581
KOLOS: NO, MAGISTRATE.

229
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:29,416
MAGISTRATE: THEN
I WILL CONSIDER THE EVIDENCE

230
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:30,958
AND DELIVER MY VERDICT--

231
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,419
ARCHER: I'D LIKE A CHANCE
TO DEFEND MYSELF.

232
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,961
MAGISTRATE:
YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED.

233
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,796
ARCHER:
HE'S DISTORTING THE TRUTH!

234
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,090
MAGISTRATE: BE SILENT!

235
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:38,799
ARCHER:
THOSE PEOPLE WEREN'T REBELS.

236
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:40,468
AND I WASN'T TRYING
TO START A REBELLION.

237
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:43,054
I AM NOT YOUR ENEMY!

238
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:46,057
UGH!

239
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:47,517
[MAGISTRATE POUNDS GAVEL]

240
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:50,937
MAGISTRATE:
THIS TRIBUNAL IS IN RECESS.

241
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,767
ARCHER: WHAT IS THIS?

242
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:30,935
KOLOS: TARG.

243
00:13:30,977 --> 00:13:33,062
ARCHER: IT'S A LITTLE UNDERDONE.

244
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:35,440
KOLOS:
I TOLD YOU TO REMAIN SILENT.

245
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:36,983
YOU SHOULD HAVE
LISTENED TO ME.

246
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,485
ARCHER: SORRY IF I INTERFERED

247
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:40,027
WITH YOUR LEGAL STRATEGY.

248
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,614
KOLOS: MY STRATEGY
MAY YET SPARE YOUR LIFE.

249
00:13:42,656 --> 00:13:44,907
I'VE SPOKEN
WITH THE MAGISTRATE.

250
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:47,661
HE'S WILLING TO SHOW YOU
MERCY IF YOU COOPERATE.

251
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:49,162
ARCHER: HOW?

252
00:13:49,203 --> 00:13:51,498
KOLOS: TELL HIM
WHERE TO FIND THE REBELS.

253
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:53,374
ARCHER: I TOLD YOU,
THEY'RE NOT REBELS.

254
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,460
KOLOS: IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT YOU BELIEVE.

255
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,504
THEY'RE SUBJECT TO THE LAWS
OF THE EMPIRE.

256
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,297
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN SAY
THAT WILL CHANGE THAT.

257
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:01,924
ARCHER: I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO SAY ANYTHING.

258
00:14:03,718 --> 00:14:05,679
KOLOS: WHERE DID YOU TAKE THEM?

259
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,347
ANOTHER SHIP?

260
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:09,683
A PLANET?

261
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:11,685
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT WILL HAPPEN

262
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:13,311
IF YOU DON'T TELL THEM?

263
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:15,980
ARCHER:
I HAVE A PRETTY GOOD IDEA.

264
00:14:16,022 --> 00:14:19,317
KOLOS: I'M OFFERING YOU
A WAY TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

265
00:14:21,319 --> 00:14:23,697
ARCHER:
LET'S SAY I DID COOPERATE.

266
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:26,825
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN
TO THESE PEOPLE?

267
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:29,910
KOLOS: THEY WOULD BE CHARGED
WITH TREASON.

268
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:32,497
ARCHER: AND END UP IN A COURT
LIKE THIS ONE?

269
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:38,586
TELL THE MAGISTRATE
I'M GONNA PASS ON HIS OFFER.

270
00:14:40,755 --> 00:14:42,965
KOLOS: ONLY A FOOL WOULD
SACRIFICE HIMSELF

271
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:44,801
FOR PEOPLE HE BARELY KNOWS.

272
00:14:44,843 --> 00:14:46,427
ARCHER: I KNOW THEM WELL ENOUGH.

273
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:48,137
THEY'RE GOOD PEOPLE.

274
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:49,889
AND I WON'T TURN THEM OVER.

275
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:52,851
IF YOU'D LET ME TESTIFY,
TELL MY SIDE OF THE STORY,

276
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,228
IT MIGHT BECOME CLEAR
WHY I HELPED THEM.

277
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:57,313
BUT FROM WHAT I'VE SEEN,
YOU'RE ALL PERFECTLY HAPPY

278
00:14:57,355 --> 00:14:59,524
TO IGNORE WHAT YOU
DON'T WANT TO HEAR.

279
00:14:59,566 --> 00:15:01,776
KOLOS: DON'T BE SO QUICK
TO ACCUSE ME OF SHARING

280
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:03,737
THEIR INTERPRETATION
OF THE LAW.

281
00:15:03,778 --> 00:15:05,864
ARCHER: NO?

282
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,408
WHAT'S YOUR INTERPRETATION?

283
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:12,412
KOLOS: I BECAME AN ADVOCATE
MANY YEARS AGO.

284
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:15,832
THEY WERE DIFFERENT TIMES.

285
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:17,792
ARCHER: BETTER OR WORSE?

286
00:15:17,834 --> 00:15:21,962
KOLOS: THE COURTS WERE
MORE WILLING TO LISTEN.

287
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:24,424
ARCHER: THEN MAYBE
YOU SHOULD REMIND THEM

288
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,760
OF THOSE DIFFERENT TIMES.

289
00:15:26,801 --> 00:15:29,637
NOTHING LIKE
A GOOD HISTORY LESSON.

290
00:15:32,724 --> 00:15:34,517
[KOLOS SIGHS]

291
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,853
KOLOS: I'M AN OLD MAN--

292
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:38,813
TOO OLD TO CHALLENGE THE RULES.

293
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:42,024
ARCHER: EVEN IF YOUR CLIENT'S
LIFE DEPENDS ON IT?

294
00:15:42,066 --> 00:15:45,612
I GET THE FEELING YOU'RE
AS FRUSTRATED AS I AM,

295
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:49,031
THAT YOU WANT TO
STAND UP TO THEM.

296
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:52,201
BUT YOU'VE GIVEN UP.

297
00:15:52,243 --> 00:15:54,078
YOU'RE AFRAID OF THEM.

298
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,789
KOLOS: I'M NOT AFRAID.

299
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:58,416
ARCHER:
THEN PROVE IT. CHALLENGE THEM.

300
00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:01,461
SHOW THEM WHAT
A REAL TRIAL IS LIKE.

301
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,606
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
IN KLINGON]

302
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:28,446
MAGISTRATE:
STRENGTH TO THE EMPIRE.

303
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:30,907
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

304
00:16:30,949 --> 00:16:33,493
MAGISTRATE: HAVE YOU INFORMED
THE ACCUSED OF OUR OFFER?

305
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:35,286
KOLOS: I HAVE.

306
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,079
MAGISTRATE: AND DOES HE
WISH TO ADDRESS THIS TRIBUNAL?

307
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,665
KOLOS: HE DOES.

308
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,708
HE WISHES TO TESTIFY
IN HIS OWN DEFENSE.

309
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,460
ORAK: I OBJECT!

310
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:44,211
THE TIME FOR TESTIMONY IS OVER.

311
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:45,839
KOLOS: WITH RESPECT TO
MAGISTRATE,

312
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,257
NO VERDICT HAS BEEN REACHED.

313
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:50,217
ORAK: IRRELEVANT! I URGE YOU
TO END THESE PROCEEDINGS.

314
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:53,095
KOLOS: I'M WITHIN MY RIGHTS
TO PRESENT FURTHER TESTIMONY.

315
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:55,515
ORAK: YOU'RE SPEAKING
OF ARCHAIC RIGHTS.

316
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:58,309
KOLOS: SURELY I DON'T NEED
TO REMIND THE MAGISTRATE

317
00:16:58,351 --> 00:17:00,812
THE JUDICIAL CHARTER
OF KOLOTH STATES

318
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:03,105
AN ADVOCATE IS ENTITLED
TO CHALLENGE THE CHARGES

319
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:05,817
AT ANY POINT
DURING THE TRIBUNAL.

320
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:07,694
TO MY KNOWLEDGE,

321
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:09,904
THAT CHARTER HAS NOT
BEEN CAST ASIDE.

322
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:12,532
FROM THE TIME OF KAHLESS,

323
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:15,284
OUR COURTS HAVE STOOD AS A FORUM

324
00:17:15,326 --> 00:17:18,788
WHERE JUSTICE
IS DISPENSED WITH HONOR!

325
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:20,623
[SPECTATORS MURMURING]

326
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:24,627
NOW, WILL MY CASE
BE HEARD OR WILL IT NOT?

327
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:27,964
MAGISTRATE: CALL YOUR WITNESS.

328
00:17:28,006 --> 00:17:29,966
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

329
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:39,893
KOLOS: IDENTIFY YOURSELF.

330
00:17:39,934 --> 00:17:41,519
ARCHER:
I'M CAPTAIN JONATHAN ARCHER

331
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:44,397
OF THE EARTH STARSHIP
"ENTERPRISE."

332
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:46,524
ORAK:
DO YOU ADMIT, CAPTAIN ARCHER,

333
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:50,444
THAT YOU GAVE AID AND COMFORT
TO A VESSEL FLEEING THE EMPIRE?

334
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,739
ARCHER:
WE ANSWERED A DISTRESS CALL.

335
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:55,992
THEY WERE STARVING.
THEIR LIFE SUPPORT WAS FAILING.

336
00:17:56,034 --> 00:17:58,578
ORAK: THEIR HEALTH
ISN'T AT ISSUE HERE.

337
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:00,413
YOU HELPED THEM TO ESCAPE!

338
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,457
KOLOS: WILL MY CLIENT
BE ALLOWED TO TESTIFY OR NOT?

339
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:06,586
MAGISTRATE: PROSECUTOR,
YOU WILL SHOW THE ADVOCATE

340
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:09,047
THE SAME RESPECT
HE HAS SHOWN YOU.

341
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:11,298
CONTINUE.

342
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:13,593
KOLOS:
RECOUNT FOR THIS TRIBUNAL

343
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:16,095
YOUR RECOLLECTION OF THE EVENTS.

344
00:18:16,136 --> 00:18:17,805
ARCHER: AS I SAID,

345
00:18:17,847 --> 00:18:19,974
WE HAD RECEIVED A DISTRESS CALL.

346
00:18:20,016 --> 00:18:22,977
MAGNIFY.

347
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:24,896
BIO-SIGNS?

348
00:18:24,938 --> 00:18:26,689
T'POL: 27.

349
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:30,818
ARCHER: ANY RESPONSE?

350
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:32,737
HOSHI: NO, SIR.

351
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:37,199
ARCHER: MALCOLM?

352
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:39,953
REED: MAIN PROPULSION'S OFFLINE.

353
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,579
LIFE SUPPORT IS FAILING.

354
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:43,372
THEY'RE IN A BAD WAY, SIR.

355
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:48,586
ARCHER:
CAN YOU DOCK WITH THEM?

356
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:50,964
TRAVIS: THEIR PORT ENGINE
IS VENTING REACTOR COOLANT.

357
00:18:51,005 --> 00:18:54,050
I COULD TRY TO COME IN
ON THE STARBOARD SIDE,

358
00:18:54,092 --> 00:18:56,218
BUT IT'LL BE TRICKY.

359
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,304
ARCHER: DO YOUR BEST.

360
00:19:02,016 --> 00:19:04,644
PATIENT: OUR WARP DRIVE FAILED
THREE WEEKS AFTER WE LEFT.

361
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:06,395
WE TRIED TO SET A COURSE

362
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,272
FOR THE NEAREST SYSTEM
AT IMPULSE,

363
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:10,024
BUT MAIN POWER WENT DOWN.

364
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:11,609
ARCHER: HOW LONG AGO WAS THAT?

365
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:13,444
PATIENT: I DON'T KNOW.

366
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:16,196
SIX WEEKS. MAYBE MORE.

367
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:19,199
WE DIVERTED AUXILIARY POWER
TO LIFE SUPPORT,

368
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:21,077
BUT IT WASN'T ENOUGH.

369
00:19:21,119 --> 00:19:24,789
FOOD PROCESSORS FAILED,
WATER RECYCLERS.

370
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:26,916
PHLOX: I'VE PUT THEM ALL ON
PROTEIN SUPPLEMENTS,

371
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,543
BUT TWO OF THEM ARE
IN SERIOUS CONDITION.

372
00:19:29,585 --> 00:19:33,213
PATIENT: WHEN WE LEFT,
THERE WERE 54 ABOARD.

373
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:36,216
ARCHER:
WHAT BROUGHT YOU OUT HERE?

374
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:40,805
PATIENT: SEVERAL YEARS AGO,
OUR COLONY WAS ANNEXED

375
00:19:40,847 --> 00:19:43,182
BY A SPECIES
WE HAD NEVER SEEN BEFORE.

376
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:46,978
THEY SAID THEY'D PROVIDE FOR US
IN EXCHANGE FOR OUR ALLEGIANCE,

377
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:49,939
THAT WE'D BECOME
A PART OF THEIR EMPIRE.

378
00:19:49,981 --> 00:19:51,691
BUT THEY STRIPPED US
OF OUR RESOURCES,

379
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:54,068
LEFT US WITH NOTHING.

380
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:56,112
WE WAITED FOR THEM TO RETURN.

381
00:19:56,154 --> 00:19:58,781
THEY SAID
THEY'D BRING FOOD, FUEL.

382
00:20:00,158 --> 00:20:03,036
THEY NEVER CAME BACK.

383
00:20:03,077 --> 00:20:05,663
KOLOS: YOU KNEW
THEY WERE FLEEING THE EMPIRE.

384
00:20:05,705 --> 00:20:08,708
ARCHER: WE KNEW THAT
THEIR COLONY HAD BEEN ABANDONED.

385
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:11,836
KOLOS: AND YOU CHOSE
TO SHOW THEM COMPASSION.

386
00:20:11,878 --> 00:20:13,462
ARCHER: THEY WERE STARVING.

387
00:20:13,504 --> 00:20:15,214
THEY WOULDN'T
HAVE LASTED ANOTHER WEEK.

388
00:20:15,255 --> 00:20:17,050
ORAK: THEY WERE
SUBJECTS OF THE EMPIRE.

389
00:20:17,091 --> 00:20:19,343
THEIR WELFARE
WAS NOT YOUR CONCERN.

390
00:20:19,385 --> 00:20:21,637
ARCHER: APPARENTLY
IT WASN'T YOURS, EITHER.

391
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:23,263
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

392
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,892
ORAK: YOU SEE THE CONTEMPT
THESE HUMANS HAVE FOR US.

393
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:28,352
HE STILL BELIEVES
HE DID NOTHING WRONG.

394
00:20:28,394 --> 00:20:31,689
KOLOS: AND PROSECUTOR ORAK
HAS YET TO PROVE THAT HE HAS.

395
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,900
ORAK: HE AIDED THESE REBELS.

396
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:37,611
AND NOW HE REFUSES TO HELP US
BRING THEM TO JUSTICE!

397
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:39,655
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

398
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:51,084
MAGISTRATE: I WILL HEAR
WHAT THE ACCUSED HAS TO SAY.

399
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:52,877
KOLOS: CONTINUE.

400
00:20:52,919 --> 00:20:55,462
ARCHER:
MY CHIEF ENGINEER HAD DETERMINED

401
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,631
THAT THEIR VESSEL
WAS BEYOND REPAIR.

402
00:20:57,673 --> 00:20:59,175
SOME OF THE CREW
WILL HAVE TO DOUBLE UP,

403
00:20:59,217 --> 00:21:01,301
BUT I THINK WE CAN
ACCOMMODATE ALL OF THEM.

404
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:03,429
T'POL: I'VE ALREADY
GIVEN THE ORDER.

405
00:21:05,098 --> 00:21:08,350
CONSIDERING THE ALTERNATIVE
WAS TO SET THE SHIP ADRIFT,

406
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:11,604
I ANTICIPATED YOUR DECISION.

407
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:13,439
WHERE DO YOU PLAN TO TAKE THEM?

408
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,982
ARCHER:
THEY WERE HEADED FOR A SYSTEM

409
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:16,609
A FEW LIGHT-YEARS FROM HERE.

410
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,318
THAT SHOULD KEEP THEM SAFE
FROM THE KLINGONS.

411
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,113
T'POL: EMPIRES TEND TO EXPAND.

412
00:21:20,154 --> 00:21:21,697
THEY MAY EVENTUALLY DISCOVER

413
00:21:21,739 --> 00:21:23,783
THEY HAVEN'T TRAVELED
FAR ENOUGH.

414
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:26,202
REED: Captain, please report
to the bridge.

415
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:36,170
ARCHER:
LOOKS LIKE THEY DIDN'T ABANDON

416
00:21:36,212 --> 00:21:38,297
THE COLONISTS AFTER ALL.

417
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:40,633
REED: PERHAPS THEY'RE BRINGING
THE SUPPLIES THEY PROMISED.

418
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:44,386
T'POL: IT'S A D5 BATTLE CRUISER.
I DOUBT IT'S BRINGING SUPPLIES.

419
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:47,140
ARCHER:
HOW LONG BEFORE THEY GET HERE?

420
00:21:47,181 --> 00:21:49,100
REED: 17 MINUTES.

421
00:21:49,142 --> 00:21:51,102
ARCHER:
ARE ALL THE REFUGEES ABOARD?

422
00:21:51,144 --> 00:21:53,146
REED: YES, SIR.

423
00:21:53,187 --> 00:21:56,565
ARCHER: CUT THEIR SHIP LOOSE
AND GO TO TACTICAL ALERT.

424
00:21:58,442 --> 00:22:02,029
ORAK: SO YOU WERE PREPARING
FOR BATTLE.

425
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:03,906
ARCHER: I WAS PREPARING
TO DEFEND MY SHIP.

426
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:06,700
KOLOS: AS ANY GOOD KLINGON
COMMANDER WOULD BE.

427
00:22:06,742 --> 00:22:08,744
ORAK:
THE ACCUSED HAS ALREADY ADMITTED

428
00:22:08,786 --> 00:22:11,205
THAT HE KNEW THE REBELS
WERE SUBJECTS OF THE EMPIRE.

429
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:13,040
ARCHER: THEY MAY HAVE BEEN
SUBJECTS OF THE EMPIRE,

430
00:22:13,082 --> 00:22:15,084
BUT IT SURE AS HELL LOOKED
LIKE YOU HAD ABANDONED THEM.

431
00:22:15,126 --> 00:22:17,711
ORAK: AND HE KNEW THE "BORTAS"
WAS COMING TO RETRIEVE THEM,

432
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,380
YET HE LAUNCHED
A DELIBERATE ATTACK

433
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:22,341
AGAINST AN IMPERIAL VESSEL!

434
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:26,220
THIS HUMAN IS GUILTY
OF MORE THAN INCITING REBELLION.

435
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:28,806
HE HAS COMMITTED AN ACT OF WAR!

436
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:31,309
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

437
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:44,113
REED: I DON'T SUPPOSE THERE'S
ANY CHANCE OF OUTRUNNING THEM.

438
00:22:44,155 --> 00:22:45,906
T'POL:
THEIR MAXIMUM SPEED IS WARP 6.

439
00:22:45,948 --> 00:22:47,700
TRAVIS: IF WE COULD DISABLE
THEIR ENGINES...

440
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:49,827
REED: SUSTAINED FIRE
FROM OUR PHASE CANNONS

441
00:22:49,869 --> 00:22:51,411
SHOULD BE ABLE TO PENETRATE
THEIR ARMOR,

442
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:53,080
BUT I DOUBT THEY'D SIT STILL

443
00:22:53,122 --> 00:22:54,999
LONG ENOUGH
TO GIVE US THE CHANCE.

444
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:57,293
ARCHER: WHAT'S THE COMPOSITION
OF THOSE RINGS?

445
00:23:01,214 --> 00:23:03,174
T'POL: NOTHING UNUSUAL.

446
00:23:03,216 --> 00:23:06,426
METHANE ICE, ISOLYTIC PLASMA,
DIAMAGNETIC DUST.

447
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:08,095
ARCHER: WHEN WE PULLED
THAT KLINGON SHIP

448
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:09,722
OUT OF THE GAS GIANT,

449
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:11,557
DID YOU GET A LOOK
AT THEIR SENSOR ARRAY?

450
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:13,600
REED: PRETTY STANDARD
MULTISPECTRAL SENSORS,

451
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:16,729
NOT TOO DIFFERENT FROM OURS.

452
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:19,606
ARCHER: IF WE COULD IGNITE
THE PLASMA IN THOSE RINGS,

453
00:23:19,648 --> 00:23:21,483
WOULD IT DISRUPT THEIR SENSORS?

454
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:23,194
REED: FOR A FEW SECONDS.

455
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:25,321
ARCHER:
A FEW SECONDS WILL HAVE TO DO.

456
00:23:25,363 --> 00:23:27,031
CAN YOU MODIFY A TORPEDO?

457
00:23:27,073 --> 00:23:28,824
REED: I BELIEVE SO.
ARCHER: HOW LONG?

458
00:23:28,866 --> 00:23:30,701
REED: HOW LONG DO I HAVE?

459
00:23:30,743 --> 00:23:32,703
T'POL: THE KLINGON SHIP WILL BE
HERE IN LESS THAN 11 MINUTES.

460
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:34,705
ARCHER: GET MOVING.

461
00:23:34,747 --> 00:23:38,458
ORAK: SO YOU LAID A TRAP
FOR THE "BORTAS."

462
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,294
ARCHER: WE HAD NO INTENTION
OF FIRING FIRST.

463
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:42,838
ORAK: OH, SUCH A NOBLE HUMAN.

464
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,299
KOLOS: I WAS ASSURED THE ACCUSED
WOULD BE ALLOWED TO SPEAK

465
00:23:45,341 --> 00:23:47,260
WITHOUT INTERRUPTION.

466
00:23:47,301 --> 00:23:48,886
ORAK: BY ALL MEANS.

467
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:53,391
I FIND HIS VERSION OF EVENTS
EXTREMELY ENTERTAINING.

468
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:55,684
[LAUGHTER]

469
00:23:57,519 --> 00:24:00,314
ARCHER: THE "BORTAS" HAD DROPPED
OUT OF WARP

470
00:24:00,356 --> 00:24:02,482
WITH THEIR WEAPONS CHARGED.

471
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:04,484
TRAVIS:
THEY'RE ON AN INTERCEPT COURSE.

472
00:24:04,526 --> 00:24:07,071
200,000 KILOMETERS AND CLOSING.

473
00:24:10,283 --> 00:24:12,243
ARCHER: HAIL THEM.

474
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:15,246
DURAS:<i> IDENTIFY YOURSELF.</i>

475
00:24:15,288 --> 00:24:17,039
ARCHER: I'M JONATHAN ARCHER,

476
00:24:17,081 --> 00:24:18,874
CAPTAIN
OF THE STARSHIP "ENTERPRISE."

477
00:24:18,916 --> 00:24:22,211
DURAS:<i> YOU'RE HARBORING</i>
<i>FUGITIVES. SURRENDER THEM.</i>

478
00:24:22,253 --> 00:24:24,338
ARCHER: I WASN'T AWARE
THEY'D COMMITTED ANY CRIME.

479
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:26,799
DURAS:<i> THEY'RE WANTED</i>
<i>FOR INCITING REBELLION.</i>

480
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,717
ARCHER: FROM WHAT I CAN TELL,

481
00:24:28,759 --> 00:24:32,012
THEY ARE IN NO CONDITION
TO INCITE ANYTHING.

482
00:24:32,054 --> 00:24:34,432
APPARENTLY THEIR COLONY
WAS ABANDONED BY YOUR--

483
00:24:34,472 --> 00:24:37,310
DURAS:<i> TURN OVER THE REBELS NOW!</i>

484
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:40,646
ARCHER: WHAT DO YOU INTEND
TO DO WITH THEM?

485
00:24:40,687 --> 00:24:42,856
DURAS:
<i>THAT'S NONE OF YOUR CONCERN.</i>

486
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:46,402
ARCHER: I'M SORRY, BUT I'M
NOT PREPARED TO HAND THEM OVER

487
00:24:46,444 --> 00:24:48,070
WITHOUT A LITTLE
MORE INFORMATION.

488
00:24:48,112 --> 00:24:50,072
IF I COULD SPEAK TO SOMEONE
IN YOUR GOVERNMENT--

489
00:24:50,114 --> 00:24:52,616
DURAS:<i> I SPEAK FOR THE EMPIRE.</i>

490
00:24:52,658 --> 00:24:55,328
ARCHER: FAIR ENOUGH.

491
00:24:55,369 --> 00:24:57,955
LET'S SIT DOWN AND TRY TO--

492
00:25:05,463 --> 00:25:08,882
REED: HULL PLATING'S AT 80%.
NO DAMAGE TO THE KLINGON SHIP.

493
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:10,843
ARCHER: HEAD INTO THE RINGS.

494
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:13,595
T'POL:
THEY'RE PURSUING. 10,000 METERS.

495
00:25:18,351 --> 00:25:21,312
T'POL: WE'RE APPROACHING A LARGE
FRAGMENT 600 METERS IN DIAMETER,

496
00:25:21,354 --> 00:25:23,939
BEARING 227 MARK 4.

497
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:27,693
ARCHER: PUT US BEHIND IT.

498
00:25:30,988 --> 00:25:33,491
REED: THEY'RE CLOSING, SIR.
4,000 METERS.

499
00:25:33,531 --> 00:25:35,451
ARCHER: STAND BY.

500
00:25:35,493 --> 00:25:38,329
REED: 3,000 METERS.

501
00:25:38,371 --> 00:25:41,374
2,000.

502
00:25:41,415 --> 00:25:43,083
800 METERS.

503
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:45,336
ARCHER: FIRE!

504
00:25:54,053 --> 00:25:56,222
REED: OUR SENSORS ARE DOWN.

505
00:25:56,263 --> 00:25:58,349
ARCHER:
LET'S HOPE THEIRS ARE, TOO.

506
00:25:58,391 --> 00:26:00,309
GET US OUT OF HERE.

507
00:26:00,351 --> 00:26:02,395
KOLOS: YOU SAY THE "BORTAS" 
FIRED FIRST.

508
00:26:02,436 --> 00:26:04,021
ARCHER: YES.

509
00:26:04,063 --> 00:26:06,273
KOLOS: AND YOU TRIED TO REACH
AN ACCOMMODATION

510
00:26:06,315 --> 00:26:07,858
WITH CAPTAIN DURAS?

511
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:09,609
ARCHER: HE REFUSED.

512
00:26:09,651 --> 00:26:11,445
ORAK:
DURAS WAS UNDER NO OBLIGATION

513
00:26:11,487 --> 00:26:13,113
TO ACCOMMODATE THIS HUMAN.

514
00:26:13,155 --> 00:26:15,115
KOLOS: SO YOU WERE SIMPLY
DEFENDING YOUR SHIP

515
00:26:15,157 --> 00:26:16,658
WHEN YOU ATTACKED THE "BORTAS"?

516
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,827
ARCHER: YES.
KOLOS: AND THEN WHAT HAPPENED?

517
00:26:18,869 --> 00:26:21,830
ARCHER: WE LEFT THE SYSTEM
AND TOOK THE REFUGEES WITH US.

518
00:26:21,872 --> 00:26:25,418
KOLOS: YOU COULD HAVE DESTROYED
THE "BORTAS."

519
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:27,253
WHY DIDN'T YOU?

520
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:30,423
ARCHER: BECAUSE CAPTAIN DURAS
IS NOT MY ENEMY.

521
00:26:30,464 --> 00:26:34,343
KOLOS: NOT YOUR ENEMY?

522
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:39,681
I SUBMIT TO THIS TRIBUNAL

523
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:43,394
THAT CAPTAIN ARCHER IS GUILTY...

524
00:26:43,436 --> 00:26:45,771
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

525
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,444
GUILTY OF MEDDLING
IN KLINGON AFFAIRS

526
00:26:51,485 --> 00:26:53,028
ON MORE THAN ONE OCCASION.

527
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:54,654
IN FACT, I'VE DISCOVERED

528
00:26:54,696 --> 00:26:57,157
HIS NAME IS WELL KNOWN
TO THE HIGH COUNCIL.

529
00:26:57,199 --> 00:27:00,578
THE ACCUSED ONCE STOOD
BEFORE THE CHANCELLOR HIMSELF

530
00:27:00,618 --> 00:27:02,913
AND EXPOSED A SULIBAN PLOT
THAT WOULD HAVE THROWN

531
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:05,165
THE EMPIRE INTO CIVIL WAR.

532
00:27:05,207 --> 00:27:06,917
ORAK: THAT IS ABSURD.

533
00:27:06,959 --> 00:27:09,627
KOLOS: THE FACTS ARE ON RECORD.

534
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:11,297
PERHAPS THE PROSECUTOR

535
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:14,883
HAS GROWN COMPLACENT
WITH HIS RESEARCH.

536
00:27:14,925 --> 00:27:17,844
THE RECORDS
OF THE IMPERIAL FLEET

537
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:19,513
ALSO MENTION THIS MAN.

538
00:27:19,555 --> 00:27:21,307
HIS SHIP WAS INSTRUMENTAL

539
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:24,935
IN THE RESCUE OF THE KLINGON
RAPTOR THE "SOMRAW"

540
00:27:24,977 --> 00:27:27,104
FROM THE DENSE ATMOSPHERE
OF A GAS GIANT.

541
00:27:27,146 --> 00:27:28,688
ORAK: EVEN IF THIS IS TRUE,

542
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:30,983
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH THIS CASE!

543
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:34,069
KOLOS: IT HAS EVERYTHING
TO DO WITH THIS CASE.

544
00:27:34,111 --> 00:27:37,114
IT SHOWS A PATTERN
IN ARCHER'S BEHAVIOR

545
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:40,367
THAT WAS REPEATED IN HIS
ENCOUNTER WITH CAPTAIN DURAS.

546
00:27:40,409 --> 00:27:44,037
YES, HE MAY BE SELF-RIGHTEOUS,

547
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:46,832
BUT HIS MEDDLING
HAS SAVED A KLINGON SHIP

548
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:50,169
AND PERHAPS THE FATE
OF THE EMPIRE ITSELF.

549
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:53,172
IF CAPTAIN ARCHER IS GUILTY,

550
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:56,049
HE IS GUILTY OF NOTHING MORE
THAN BEING A NUISANCE

551
00:27:56,091 --> 00:28:00,471
AND HARDLY WORTH
THE ATTENTION OF THIS TRIBUNAL.

552
00:28:00,513 --> 00:28:02,515
AND IF HE MUST BE PUNISHED,

553
00:28:02,556 --> 00:28:06,268
LET THE PUNISHMENT FIT
THAT CRIME.

554
00:28:09,605 --> 00:28:12,816
ARCHER: HOW LONG SHOULD IT TAKE
FOR A VERDICT?

555
00:28:12,858 --> 00:28:16,362
KOLOS: IT USUALLY DOESN'T
TAKE LONG AT ALL.

556
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:19,239
I MUST HAVE BEEN MORE
PERSUASIVE THAN I THOUGHT.

557
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:22,326
[KOLOS CHUCKLES]

558
00:28:22,368 --> 00:28:26,163
ARCHER: THANKS FOR WHAT YOU'VE
DONE FOR ME.

559
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:28,706
KOLOS: OH, DON'T THANK ME YET.

560
00:28:28,748 --> 00:28:32,127
THE ODDS ARE STILL
VERY MUCH AGAINST US.

561
00:28:36,549 --> 00:28:39,385
ARCHER: WHAT IS IT?
KOLOS: BLOODWINE.

562
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:42,638
IT SHOULD HELP MAKE
THE WAIT MORE PLEASANT.

563
00:28:50,604 --> 00:28:52,314
ARCHER: WHAT'S IT THE BLOOD OF?

564
00:28:52,356 --> 00:28:53,940
[KOLOS CHUCKLES]

565
00:28:53,982 --> 00:28:56,943
KOLOS: DON'T FEEL BADLY
IF YOU CAN'T STOMACH IT.

566
00:28:58,070 --> 00:29:00,197
ARCHER: I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

567
00:29:10,874 --> 00:29:13,419
HOW MANY CASES HAVE YOU WON?

568
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:16,589
KOLOS: OH, I'M NOT SURE.

569
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:18,840
OVER 200.

570
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:21,801
BUT THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO,

571
00:29:21,843 --> 00:29:24,304
WHEN THE TRIBUNAL
WAS A FORUM FOR THE TRUTH

572
00:29:24,346 --> 00:29:27,391
AND NOT A TOOL
FOR THE WARRIOR CLASS.

573
00:29:30,519 --> 00:29:33,480
ARCHER: THERE ARE OTHER CLASSES?

574
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:37,067
KOLOS: YOU DIDN'T BELIEVE
ALL KLINGONS WERE SOLDIERS?

575
00:29:38,652 --> 00:29:40,487
ARCHER: I GUESS I DID.

576
00:29:40,529 --> 00:29:42,489
KOLOS: AH.

577
00:29:42,531 --> 00:29:46,243
MY FATHER WAS A TEACHER,

578
00:29:46,285 --> 00:29:49,788
MY MOTHER A BIOLOGIST
AT THE UNIVERSITY.

579
00:29:49,829 --> 00:29:55,001
THEY ENCOURAGED ME
TO TAKE UP THE LAW.

580
00:29:55,043 --> 00:30:01,133
NOW ALL YOUNG PEOPLE
WANT TO DO IS TAKE UP WEAPONS

581
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:03,176
AS SOON AS THEY
CAN HOLD THEM.

582
00:30:03,218 --> 00:30:08,682
THEY'RE TOLD THERE'S HONOR
IN VICTORY, ANY VICTORY.

583
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:10,643
BUT WHAT HONOR IS THERE

584
00:30:10,684 --> 00:30:13,646
IN A VICTORY
OVER A WEAKER OPPONENT?

585
00:30:13,687 --> 00:30:16,482
HAD DURAS DESTROYED THAT SHIP,

586
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:19,901
HE WOULD HAVE BEEN LAUDED
AS A HERO OF THE EMPIRE

587
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:23,322
FOR MURDERING HELPLESS REFUGEES.

588
00:30:23,363 --> 00:30:24,823
[KOLOS SIGHS]

589
00:30:24,864 --> 00:30:30,621
WE WERE A GREAT SOCIETY
NOT SO LONG AGO,

590
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:32,831
WHEN HONOR WAS EARNED

591
00:30:32,872 --> 00:30:38,253
THROUGH INTEGRITY
AND ACTS OF TRUE COURAGE,

592
00:30:38,295 --> 00:30:41,214
NOT SENSELESS BLOODSHED.

593
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:46,178
ARCHER: FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS,
MY PEOPLE HAD SIMILAR PROBLEMS.

594
00:30:46,219 --> 00:30:49,682
WE FOUGHT THREE WORLD WARS
THAT ALMOST DESTROYED US.

595
00:30:49,723 --> 00:30:52,434
WHOLE GENERATIONS
WERE NEARLY WIPED OUT.

596
00:30:52,476 --> 00:30:54,728
KOLOS: WHAT CHANGED?

597
00:30:56,355 --> 00:31:01,735
ARCHER: A FEW COURAGEOUS PEOPLE
BEGAN TO REALIZE

598
00:31:01,777 --> 00:31:03,903
THEY COULD MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

599
00:31:05,656 --> 00:31:07,700
[LOCK TURNS]

600
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:24,508
MAGISTRATE: I HAVE WEIGHED
THE EVIDENCE CAREFULLY.

601
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:27,761
ADVOCATE KOLOS HAS MADE
AN IMPRESSIVE CASE

602
00:31:27,803 --> 00:31:31,515
MUCH TO THE SURPRISE
OF THIS TRIBUNAL.

603
00:31:31,557 --> 00:31:35,310
BASED UPON HIS ARGUMENTS,
I AM INCLINED TO BELIEVE

604
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:38,938
THAT THE ACCUSED WAS A VICTIM
OF HIS OWN FOOLISHNESS.

605
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:42,359
HE WAS NOT FOMENTING REBELLION.

606
00:31:42,401 --> 00:31:47,573
BUT, AS PROSECUTOR ORAK
HAS MADE CLEAR,

607
00:31:47,614 --> 00:31:50,950
THE LAWS OF THE EMPIRE
HAVE BEEN VIOLATED.

608
00:31:50,992 --> 00:31:53,203
AND CAPTAIN ARCHER
MUST BE HELD ACCOUNTABLE

609
00:31:53,245 --> 00:31:55,121
FOR HIS ACTIONS

610
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:57,750
REGARDLESS OF HIS INTENT.

611
00:31:57,791 --> 00:32:02,379
I THEREFORE FIND THE ACCUSED
GUILTY AS CHARGED.

612
00:32:02,421 --> 00:32:05,090
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

613
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:09,052
MAGISTRATE: HOWEVER...

614
00:32:10,679 --> 00:32:12,598
HOWEVER...

615
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:16,769
THIS TRIBUNAL
CANNOT IGNORE HIS ACTIONS

616
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:19,062
ASSISTING THE KLINGON PEOPLE.

617
00:32:19,104 --> 00:32:24,025
THEREFORE, THE SENTENCE OF DEATH
IS COMMUTED.

618
00:32:24,067 --> 00:32:26,403
[KLINGONS GRUMBLING]

619
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:31,909
MAGISTRATE: SILENCE!

620
00:32:33,493 --> 00:32:36,789
JONATHAN ARCHER,

621
00:32:36,830 --> 00:32:39,625
YOU ARE CONDEMNED
TO THE DILITHIUM MINES

622
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:43,420
ON THE PENAL COLONY
OF RURA PENTHE

623
00:32:43,462 --> 00:32:45,923
FOR THE REMAINDER OF YOUR LIFE.

624
00:32:59,352 --> 00:33:01,229
MAGISTRATE: REMOVE THE PRISONER.

625
00:33:01,271 --> 00:33:03,189
ORAK: I PROTEST.

626
00:33:03,231 --> 00:33:05,442
MAGISTRATE: I WOULDN'T PROTEST
TOO LOUDLY, PROSECUTOR.

627
00:33:05,484 --> 00:33:07,444
YOU'VE WON YOUR CASE.

628
00:33:07,486 --> 00:33:09,112
ORAK: AND I COMPLIMENT
THE MAGISTRATE

629
00:33:09,154 --> 00:33:10,823
ON HIS JUST RULING.

630
00:33:10,864 --> 00:33:14,117
BUT THE SENTENCE
FOR THESE CRIMES MUST BE DEATH.

631
00:33:14,159 --> 00:33:16,244
KOLOS: THE SENTENCE IS DEATH.

632
00:33:16,286 --> 00:33:19,247
YOU CONDEMN THIS MAN
TO RURA PENTHE.

633
00:33:19,289 --> 00:33:22,793
WHAT IS THE LIFE EXPECTANCY
OF A PRISONER THERE?

634
00:33:22,835 --> 00:33:25,378
SIX MONTHS,
A YEAR AT THE MOST?

635
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:29,132
AND YOU EXPECT US TO BELIEVE
THAT THIS IS AN ACT OF MERCY.

636
00:33:29,174 --> 00:33:30,968
MAGISTRATE:
THIS COURT HAS SHOWN YOU

637
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:33,094
A GREAT DEAL
OF PATIENCE, ADVOCATE.

638
00:33:33,136 --> 00:33:35,722
DON'T TEST MY LIMITS
ANY FURTHER.

639
00:33:35,764 --> 00:33:38,099
KOLOS: I ASK
FOR NO SPECIAL TREATMENT,

640
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:41,520
ONLY THAT MY CLIENT
BE JUDGED FAIRLY,

641
00:33:41,561 --> 00:33:43,814
AS ANY KLINGON WOULD BE JUDGED.

642
00:33:43,856 --> 00:33:46,149
BUT IT HAS BEEN MANY YEARS

643
00:33:46,191 --> 00:33:48,318
SINCE ANYONE STOOD
IN THIS CHAMBER

644
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:50,069
AND RECEIVED JUSTICE.

645
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:52,280
MAGISTRATE: WATCH YOUR WORDS.

646
00:33:52,322 --> 00:33:55,408
YOU INSULT THE HONOR
OF THIS TRIBUNAL.

647
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:57,953
KOLOS: HONOR?!

648
00:33:57,995 --> 00:34:01,080
YOU ACKNOWLEDGE
THAT CAPTAIN ARCHER

649
00:34:01,122 --> 00:34:03,750
ACTED WITH CONVICTION
AND INTEGRITY.

650
00:34:03,792 --> 00:34:05,585
AND HOW DO YOU REWARD HIM?

651
00:34:05,627 --> 00:34:10,298
WITH THIS GRAND PUBLIC
DISPLAY OF COMPASSION

652
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:14,678
BEFORE SENDING HIM TO HIS DEATH
IN A FROZEN CAVE!

653
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:16,513
MAGISTRATE: ENOUGH!

654
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:20,475
KOLOS: FORGIVE ME IF I FAIL
TO SEE THE HONOR IN THAT!

655
00:34:20,517 --> 00:34:23,311
MAGISTRATE: YOU ARE IN CONTEMPT
OF THIS TRIBUNAL.

656
00:34:23,353 --> 00:34:27,148
SINCE YOU HAVE SUCH ADMIRATION
FOR THE PRISONER,

657
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:32,988
YOU WILL JOIN HIM ON RURA PENTHE
FOR A PERIOD OF ONE YEAR.

658
00:34:33,030 --> 00:34:35,741
[SPECTATORS SHOUTING]

659
00:34:35,782 --> 00:34:37,784
REMOVE THEM BOTH.

660
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:50,839
T'POL: THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND

661
00:34:50,881 --> 00:34:53,258
WILL CONTINUE TO LOBBY
FOR THE CAPTAIN'S RELEASE.

662
00:34:53,299 --> 00:34:55,510
TUCKER: SO WHAT DO WE DO?

663
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:57,596
T'POL: THE KLINGONS HAVE
ONLY ALLOWED US TO REMAIN HERE

664
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,890
DURING THE TRIAL.

665
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,808
WE'RE TO LEAVE IMMEDIATELY.

666
00:35:01,850 --> 00:35:03,685
REED: AND ABANDON THE CAPTAIN?

667
00:35:03,727 --> 00:35:05,812
T'POL: WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

668
00:35:05,854 --> 00:35:08,356
TRAVIS:
WHAT'S THIS RURA PENTHE LIKE?

669
00:35:08,398 --> 00:35:10,817
T'POL: IT'S QUITE INHOSPITABLE.

670
00:35:10,859 --> 00:35:13,737
REED: THEY'RE GONNA HAVE
TO GET THERE.

671
00:35:13,779 --> 00:35:16,155
T'POL: WE'RE DEEP INSIDE
KLINGON TERRITORY.

672
00:35:16,197 --> 00:35:20,077
A RESCUE ATTEMPT
IS OUT OF THE QUESTION.

673
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:21,453
TUCKER: I'M WILLING TO RISK IT.

674
00:35:21,494 --> 00:35:23,288
T'POL: THE CAPTAIN ISN'T.

675
00:35:23,329 --> 00:35:25,373
HE MADE IT CLEAR
HE DIDN'T WANT US

676
00:35:25,415 --> 00:35:28,334
TO ENDANGER THE CREW
ON HIS BEHALF.

677
00:35:28,376 --> 00:35:30,587
TUCKER: SO YOU'RE SAYING WE
JUST FORGET ABOUT HIM?

678
00:35:30,629 --> 00:35:32,965
T'POL: I'M SAYING A RESCUE
ISN'T AN OPTION.

679
00:35:33,006 --> 00:35:35,050
BUT THERE ARE
DIPLOMATIC CHANNELS.

680
00:35:35,092 --> 00:35:37,594
TUCKER:
WE TRIED DIPLOMATIC CHANNELS.

681
00:35:37,636 --> 00:35:39,554
T'POL: NOT ALL OF THEM.

682
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:42,015
I'VE DEALT WITH SEVERAL KLINGON
BUREAUCRATS IN THE PAST.

683
00:35:42,057 --> 00:35:45,435
SOME OF THEM CAN BE PERSUADED.

684
00:35:47,312 --> 00:35:49,397
MR. MAYWEATHER.

685
00:35:53,401 --> 00:35:55,361
TAKE US OUT OF ORBIT.

686
00:35:57,739 --> 00:36:00,867
[WIND]

687
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:13,088
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

688
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:15,841
GUARD: YOU, GET BACK TO WORK!

689
00:36:24,307 --> 00:36:26,559
[KOLOS BREATHING HEAVILY]

690
00:36:30,105 --> 00:36:32,107
ARCHER: YOU ALL RIGHT?

691
00:36:33,859 --> 00:36:37,821
KOLOS: PERHAPS I SPENT TOO MUCH
TIME IN THE LAW LIBRARY

692
00:36:37,863 --> 00:36:40,657
AND NOT ENOUGH
IN THE BATTLEFIELD.

693
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:44,243
ARCHER: NOT ALL KLINGONS
ARE WARRIORS, REMEMBER?

694
00:36:44,285 --> 00:36:45,662
KOLOS: AAH!

695
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:50,167
GUARD: OUR SHIPS RUN
ON DILITHIUM, NOT TALK.

696
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:52,210
KOLOS: UH!
ARCHER: LEAVE HIM ALONE.

697
00:36:52,251 --> 00:36:54,212
GUARD: GET BACK TO WORK.

698
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,688
DIFFERENT GUARD:
ANY MORE TROUBLE FROM YOU

699
00:37:11,730 --> 00:37:14,066
AND YOU'LL SPEND THE NIGHT
ON THE SURFACE.

700
00:37:14,107 --> 00:37:17,276
[ARCHER GROANING]

701
00:37:22,532 --> 00:37:24,784
KOLOS: Y-YOU'RE A FOOL.

702
00:37:26,285 --> 00:37:28,038
ARCHER: YOU'RE WELCOME.

703
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:29,915
KOLOS: HAVEN'T YOU LEARNED
YOUR LESSON?

704
00:37:29,956 --> 00:37:32,084
THIS IS WHY YOU WERE SENT
HERE IN THE FIRST PLACE--

705
00:37:32,125 --> 00:37:35,712
FOR INTERFERING IN AFFAIRS THAT
HAVE NOTHING TO DO WITH YOU.

706
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:37,839
ARCHER: WE HAVE
A SAYING ON EARTH--

707
00:37:37,881 --> 00:37:41,342
YOU DON'T KICK A MAN
WHEN HE'S DOWN.

708
00:37:41,384 --> 00:37:46,223
KOLOS:
SO ARE ALL HUMANS LIKE THIS?

709
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:49,017
ARCHER: LIKE WHAT? FAIR?

710
00:37:49,059 --> 00:37:51,519
KOLOS: STUPID.

711
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:56,108
[LAUGHTER]

712
00:38:00,486 --> 00:38:02,655
ARCHER: IT'S IN OUR NATURE.

713
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:06,118
KOLOS: STAND UP.

714
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:08,411
WE HAVE WORK TO DO...

715
00:38:10,747 --> 00:38:14,375
UNLESS YOU WANT TO SLEEP
ON THE SURFACE.

716
00:38:39,192 --> 00:38:40,819
[DOOR OPENS]

717
00:38:40,860 --> 00:38:42,988
GUARD: FOLLOW ME. THIS WAY.

718
00:38:43,029 --> 00:38:45,907
ARCHER: NEW ARRIVALS.

719
00:38:49,911 --> 00:38:52,580
KOLOS: PROSECUTOR ORAK
HAS BEEN BUSY.

720
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:28,325
STAY AWAY FROM US.
WE HAVE NOTHING YOU WANT.

721
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:32,162
REED: CAPTAIN!
ARCHER: IT'S ALL RIGHT.

722
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:35,999
HE'S FROM MY SHIP.

723
00:39:36,041 --> 00:39:38,168
REED: IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU, SIR.

724
00:39:38,210 --> 00:39:39,752
ARCHER: YOU, TOO.

725
00:39:39,794 --> 00:39:41,963
LIEUTENANT REED,
THIS IS KOLOS, MY ADVOCATE.

726
00:39:42,005 --> 00:39:44,049
[KOLOS GRUNTS]

727
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,009
REED: PLEASURE.
ARCHER: HOW'D YOU GET HERE?

728
00:39:46,051 --> 00:39:48,053
REED: T'POL KNOWS A FEW
KLINGON OFFICIALS

729
00:39:48,094 --> 00:39:50,388
FROM HER DAYS
IN THE MINISTRY OF SECURITY.

730
00:39:50,429 --> 00:39:52,098
ONE OF THEM PUT US IN TOUCH
WITH A CORRECTIONS OFFICER

731
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:53,725
WHO WAS WILLING TO
LOOK THE OTHER WAY

732
00:39:53,766 --> 00:39:55,227
FOR THE RIGHT PRICE.

733
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:57,187
I CAME ON ONE
OF THE DILITHIUM BARGES.

734
00:39:57,229 --> 00:39:59,564
WE BRIBED THE CAPTAIN
TO BRING US HERE

735
00:39:59,605 --> 00:40:01,149
AND TAKE US BACK
TO "ENTERPRISE."

736
00:40:01,191 --> 00:40:03,193
ARCHER: IS THERE ROOM
FOR ONE MORE?

737
00:40:03,235 --> 00:40:06,696
REED: I IMAGINE SO.
BUT WE HAVE TO HURRY.

738
00:40:06,738 --> 00:40:08,156
ARCHER: COME ON.

739
00:40:08,198 --> 00:40:09,824
KOLOS: I CAN'T GO WITH YOU.

740
00:40:09,866 --> 00:40:12,077
ARCHER: WHY NOT?

741
00:40:12,118 --> 00:40:15,496
KOLOS: I'VE BEEN AN ADVOCATE
FOR 50 YEARS.

742
00:40:15,538 --> 00:40:17,498
AND I SPENT THE LAST 20 OF THEM

743
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:19,500
STANDING IN THAT TRIBUNAL,

744
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:23,588
PLAYING MY PART,
HOLDING MY TONGUE,

745
00:40:23,629 --> 00:40:25,215
AND ALL THE WHILE,

746
00:40:25,257 --> 00:40:27,842
HONORABLE MEN WERE BEING SENT
TO PLACES LIKE THIS

747
00:40:27,884 --> 00:40:30,303
WITHOUT THE BENEFIT
OF A DEFENSE.

748
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:33,306
AND THEN I WAS
ASSIGNED YOUR CASE.

749
00:40:33,348 --> 00:40:35,850
YOU TOLD ME THAT ON YOUR WORLD,

750
00:40:35,892 --> 00:40:39,645
A FEW COURAGEOUS PEOPLE
MADE A DIFFERENCE.

751
00:40:39,687 --> 00:40:42,481
I'M NOT SURE
I HAVE THE COURAGE,

752
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:47,528
BUT I KNOW I'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO RESTORE HONOR TO MY PEOPLE

753
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:50,823
LIVING AS A FUGITIVE.

754
00:40:50,865 --> 00:40:52,867
ARCHER:
YOU REALIZE WHAT THAT MEANS.

755
00:40:52,909 --> 00:40:58,497
YOU SAID MOST PRISONERS HERE
DON'T SURVIVE A YEAR.

756
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:03,962
KOLOS: MOST PRISONERS HERE HAVE
VERY LITTLE TO LIVE FOR.

757
00:41:04,003 --> 00:41:06,423
REED: CAPTAIN?

758
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:08,300
KOLOS: GO.

759
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:11,803
GO!

760
00:41:13,512 --> 00:41:15,681
ARCHER: THANK YOU.
